1
00:00:01,240 --> 00:00:04,520
Our brother has answered his call and gone home to the heavens.

2
00:00:05,020 --> 00:00:06,560
What lies here in this casket

3
00:00:06,560 --> 00:00:09,580
is nothing more than the physical shell of Richard Brown.

4
00:00:09,860 --> 00:00:11,940
We know his soul has been set free.

5
00:00:12,320 --> 00:00:13,980
It will go on and live forever.

6
00:00:14,680 --> 00:00:16,120
Let us embrace his memory,

7
00:00:16,800 --> 00:00:19,020
remembering that wherever his family will be,

8
00:00:19,520 --> 00:00:21,840
this loving father and hard-working husband

9
00:00:21,840 --> 00:00:24,040
will always be there in spirit.

10
00:00:24,960 --> 00:00:26,900
After he had risen from the dead,

11
00:00:27,540 --> 00:00:29,380
It doesn't make any sense.

12
00:00:31,240 --> 00:00:33,040
He just left so much unfinished.

13
00:00:34,060 --> 00:00:36,380
I'm shocked that no one from the police force is here.

14
00:00:36,720 --> 00:00:38,140
Richard was an excellent detective,

15
00:00:38,300 --> 00:00:40,320
but not one of them came to pay their respects.

16
00:00:40,860 --> 00:00:41,940
It's ironic about him.

17
00:00:42,300 --> 00:00:44,140
Drinking on duty cost him his career,

18
00:00:44,640 --> 00:00:47,680
and in the end, a drunken fall is what cost him his life.

19
00:00:48,000 --> 00:00:50,000
At least, that's what the police report said.

20
00:00:50,420 --> 00:00:52,240
His voice was so alive when he called.

21
00:00:52,600 --> 00:00:54,620
He was very excited about seeing his daughter,

22
00:00:54,740 --> 00:00:56,180
but he never quite made it.

23
00:00:56,900 --> 00:01:00,580
The Holy Spirit has planted in each of us a seed of immortality.

24
00:01:02,300 --> 00:01:06,780
I asked myself, "Did I really do everything I could to help poor Richard?"

25
00:01:06,780 --> 00:01:08,360
Why, of course you did, Doctor.

26
00:01:08,680 --> 00:01:11,500
I just sat there listening to him spill out his life to me,

27
00:01:11,600 --> 00:01:14,540
and I told him he was well on his way to making a full recovery.

28
00:01:15,960 --> 00:01:19,860
I was wrong. I feel like I never did enough to help him.

29
00:01:21,840 --> 00:01:23,040
Tenma is the key.

30
00:01:23,040 --> 00:01:27,440
If we could question him, we might get the answers to help us solve all of this.

31
00:01:27,720 --> 00:01:29,020
I do believe you're right.

32
00:01:29,640 --> 00:01:32,140
I think there's something we both know, Doctor.

33
00:01:32,660 --> 00:01:35,280
This wasn't an accident or a suicide.

34
00:01:35,880 --> 00:01:40,740
As you said, a few hours before his death, Richard was on the phone happily talking to his daughter.

35
00:01:41,420 --> 00:01:42,640
He wanted to see her.

36
00:01:46,320 --> 00:01:49,220
Doctor, you did all that you could and you had helped him.

37
00:01:49,560 --> 00:01:52,080
Richard had quit drinking and was on the road to recovery.

38
00:01:58,060 --> 00:02:02,300
"Whatever happened, it wasn't your fault."

39
00:03:06,820 --> 00:03:07,960
(dramatic music)

40
