42
00:03:42,840 --> 00:03:46,260
I'm serious. I found out my husband's having an affair.

43
00:03:46,500 --> 00:03:49,740
So I confronted him, and now he won't even speak to me.

44
00:03:49,820 --> 00:03:53,580
He just washes the car, cleans the garage, and gives me the silent treatment.

45
00:03:53,960 --> 00:03:56,480
I know he's avoiding me. It's so obvious.

46
00:03:56,940 --> 00:04:00,140
I wait up for him to come to bed, but he falls asleep in his chair.

47
00:04:00,320 --> 00:04:03,400
Besides being blonde and beautiful, what's she got that I don't?

48
00:04:04,340 --> 00:04:06,520
Doctor, are you listening to me?

49
00:04:06,820 --> 00:04:09,480
Uh, of course. Please, continue.

50
00:04:09,820 --> 00:04:12,260
Now here's the part you were just not going to believe.

51
00:04:12,540 --> 00:04:17,240
I decided to confront this other woman, so I go over to her place, and what do you think she said to me?

52
00:04:22,080 --> 00:04:26,240
A homicide? No, not a chance, Doc. It was an unlucky accident.

53
00:04:27,360 --> 00:04:32,440
Richard Brown was alone that evening when he went up to the roof of building number 12 at Munich University.

54
00:04:32,440 --> 00:04:36,840
He polished off a bottle of whiskey, and he got so drunk he fell off the roof.

55
00:04:36,960 --> 00:04:37,760
End of story.

56
00:04:38,080 --> 00:04:40,860
The bottle. Did you have it thoroughly examined?

57
00:04:41,580 --> 00:04:45,120
Yes, of course we did, and we found Richard's prints on it.

58
00:04:45,340 --> 00:04:47,740
If you don't mind, could I see that bottle?

59
