Get in touch with us?

201
00:14:14,440 --> 00:14:15,040
- Absolutely.

202
00:14:15,460 --> 00:14:18,300
If Dr. Temma sees the ad, he'll definitely contact me.

203
00:14:18,500 --> 00:14:19,980
I worded it so it would be something

204
00:14:19,980 --> 00:14:21,840
that only he and I would know about.

205
00:14:22,200 --> 00:14:22,840
- I see.

206
00:14:23,640 --> 00:14:24,860
- Now, doctor, please,

207
00:14:25,180 --> 00:14:27,180
don't make any moves until we hear from him.

208
00:14:27,980 --> 00:14:28,460
- Understood.

209
00:14:29,140 --> 00:14:30,800
But there's still one related matter

210
00:14:30,800 --> 00:14:31,960
that I need to investigate.

211
00:14:32,780 --> 00:14:33,400
- What's that?

212
00:14:33,920 --> 00:14:36,100
- This prostitute who pretended to be Margot Langer

213
00:14:36,100 --> 00:14:37,360
just might have answers.

214
00:14:38,020 --> 00:14:40,300
I'm following up on something Richard said.

215
00:14:40,840 --> 00:14:42,880
- That prostitute told me that when foreign,

216
00:14:43,300 --> 00:14:46,440
The man who killed himself went to see her. He had a young man accompanying him.

217
00:14:47,000 --> 00:14:49,340
He was a young, beautiful guy with blonde hair.

218
00:14:51,420 --> 00:14:53,700
Whatever you do, please be careful.

219
00:14:54,300 --> 00:14:59,280
Oh, I will. If I want to get to the bottom of this, I'll have to be very cautious.

220
00:14:59,900 --> 00:15:02,320
But Richard's memory deserves no less.

221
00:15:03,260 --> 00:15:05,420
Well, I'll call you later, Doctor.

222
00:15:14,380 --> 00:15:15,500
(wind howling)

223
00:15:18,080 --> 00:15:18,820
- Oh, no.

224
00:15:19,940 --> 00:15:22,540
So, Amerith, today you forget to shut the window.

225
00:15:25,600 --> 00:15:26,720
(men laughing)

226
00:15:28,380 --> 00:15:31,040
- Margot Langerholt, never heard of her.

227
00:15:31,600 --> 00:15:35,020
- Well, I understand she goes by the name of Sophie

228
00:15:35,020 --> 00:15:36,400
or something like that.

229
00:15:36,580 --> 00:15:39,360
- Oh, yeah, so you want that fat old hat?

230
00:15:39,620 --> 00:15:41,400
Is that what floats your boat, Gramps?

231
00:15:43,340 --> 00:15:48,780
Oh, you're blushing fine make a ride two blocks down the brick building second floor

232
