260
00:17:10,800 --> 00:17:14,900
If I can get her to confirm that this Johan was actually with Farren,

261
00:17:14,980 --> 00:17:17,260
I'll have someone who can testify to that fact,

262
00:17:17,380 --> 00:17:20,100
which would bring me closer to getting to the bottom of this mess.

263
00:17:23,800 --> 00:17:24,200
Yes?

264
00:17:24,900 --> 00:17:27,900
Yeah, my wife booked a session for me. Last name's Hess.

265
00:17:28,040 --> 00:17:29,780
I buzzed the door. Please come in.

266
00:17:33,160 --> 00:17:36,760
I might have better luck tonight if I go down there and look for Sophie again.

267
00:17:36,900 --> 00:17:37,680
It's worth a shot.

268
00:17:40,400 --> 00:17:42,560
Good evening, Dr. Reichlein.

269
00:17:42,760 --> 00:17:44,420
Mr. Hess. Ah, welcome.

270
00:17:44,820 --> 00:17:46,360
It's, uh, nice to meet you.

271
00:17:46,740 --> 00:17:47,840
Please, sit down.

272
00:17:48,140 --> 00:17:51,920
I, uh, this is my first time in counseling, so...

273
00:17:51,920 --> 00:17:53,880
Well, there's nothing to be nervous about.

274
00:17:54,300 --> 00:17:55,860
All you need to do is relax.

275
00:17:55,960 --> 00:17:57,780
We're here to talk about whatever you want.

276
00:17:58,120 --> 00:18:01,520
You can rest assured that our conversation will be completely confidential.

277
00:18:01,860 --> 00:18:03,560
What we talk about stays right here.

278
00:18:03,980 --> 00:18:05,680
You won't tell my wife?

279
00:18:06,060 --> 00:18:06,780
Of course not.

280
00:18:09,000 --> 00:18:13,080
How have you been feeling lately, and what is it you worry about?

281
00:18:13,780 --> 00:18:14,280
My worries?

282
00:18:14,920 --> 00:18:15,680
Yes, yours.

283
00:18:18,100 --> 00:18:21,660
Well, my wife, she found out about my affair.

284
00:18:22,020 --> 00:18:23,020
And your feeling?

285
00:18:23,460 --> 00:18:25,960
I feel like I'm a stranger in my own home.

286
00:18:26,600 --> 00:18:28,780
I just wash the car and clean up the garage.

287
00:18:29,560 --> 00:18:31,660
That's all I do every day.

288
00:18:32,020 --> 00:18:34,520
Does doing things around the house make you feel better?

289
00:18:34,520 --> 00:18:39,400
Not really. And it seems like I hardly ever talk to my wife anymore.

290
00:18:39,980 --> 00:18:42,560
Do you want to talk to her, but can't find a way to?

291
00:18:43,400 --> 00:18:45,920
Well, I... I don't know about that.

292
00:18:46,220 --> 00:18:47,720
Well, what about the mistress?

293
00:18:48,480 --> 00:18:48,940
What?

294
00:18:49,520 --> 00:18:52,560
You know, the woman you had an affair with. Have you two...

295
00:18:52,560 --> 00:18:55,740
Yeah. I guess so. I killed her.

296
00:18:56,260 --> 00:18:56,540
Hmm?

297
00:18:57,540 --> 00:19:00,400
Well, I mean I had a dream where I killed her.

298
00:19:00,760 --> 00:19:03,840
So how often would you say you have those kinds of dreams?

299
00:19:04,520 --> 00:19:09,440
Oh, not often. Just once. I really don't have many dreams, Doc.

300
00:19:11,840 --> 00:19:13,940
Guess I did it 'cause I was lonely.

301
00:19:18,480 --> 00:19:20,960
Is that the reason you chose to have an affair?

302
00:19:22,860 --> 00:19:25,720
No. It happened after I met him.

303
00:19:26,440 --> 00:19:27,260
Met who?

304
00:19:27,640 --> 00:19:31,780
I met this really beautiful young man with blonde hair.

305
00:19:35,720 --> 00:19:39,080
Before he showed up, I felt like I was living underwater.

306
00:19:40,100 --> 00:19:45,000
No matter how many people I killed, even after the wall fell, it was as if I was in a dream.

307
00:19:49,380 --> 00:19:51,720
After that, everything was a lot more real.

308
00:19:52,560 --> 00:19:54,820
I didn't feel like I was all alone anymore.

309
00:20:03,620 --> 00:20:06,680
Uh, would you like some hot tea, perhaps?

310
00:20:07,540 --> 00:20:09,120
No, thank you. I'm fine.

311
00:20:10,780 --> 00:20:13,400
Well, I could use some. I'm feeling a bit thirsty.

312
00:20:14,180 --> 00:20:15,340
You can just wait here.

313
00:20:23,360 --> 00:20:24,800
My secretary's already gone home.

314
00:20:24,820 --> 00:20:35,520
for the day. She has a date. She really knows how to brew tea. It's too bad she's not here

315
00:20:35,520 --> 00:20:49,780
to make it for us. Hey Doc. Yes? What is it? I figure your job's gotta be pretty tough.

316
00:20:49,780 --> 00:20:51,400
I mean, there's a lot of pressure.

317
00:20:52,100 --> 00:20:54,780
People telling you all about their dreams and secrets.

318
00:20:58,100 --> 00:21:00,780
Including ones that you probably don't want to know about.

319
00:21:01,180 --> 00:21:03,560
You know, ones that could get you into trouble.

320
00:21:06,340 --> 00:21:07,100
Like mine.

321
00:21:07,660 --> 00:21:10,440
I mean, now you have to walk around knowing I'm a hitman.

322
00:21:20,360 --> 00:21:25,040
So, anyhow, if you want to make amends towards your wife...

323
00:21:27,580 --> 00:21:30,360
You... you need to start talking with her.

324
00:21:32,420 --> 00:21:35,280
I hope you forgot to lock that damn door, Merith!

325
00:21:51,560 --> 00:21:52,920
[PANTING]

